    <h2 id="what-is-tongkat-ali">What Is Tongkat Ali and Why Has It Exploded in Popularity?</h2>

    <p>Tongkat ali (<em>Eurycoma longifolia</em>) is a flowering plant native to the tropical rainforests of Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, and Vietnam. Its root bark has been used in traditional Southeast Asian medicine for centuries as a powerful tonic for energy, virility, and stress resilience. In the past two years, tongkat ali has transitioned from niche biohacking ingredient to mainstream supplement — driven largely by endorsements from neuroscientist Andrew Huberman on his Huberman Lab podcast and a growing body of clinical evidence supporting its effects on testosterone, cortisol, and body composition.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
