        <strong>Eurycomanone: the key bioactive</strong>
        <p>The primary quassinoid compound responsible for tongkat ali's testosterone and cortisol effects. Standardized products should contain a minimum of 2% eurycomanone by weight for reliable efficacy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>SHBG reduction mechanism</strong>
        <p>Tongkat ali reduces sex hormone-binding globulin, releasing bound testosterone into its active free form. This increases bioavailable testosterone without increasing total production — a safer hormonal optimization approach.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Cortisol reduction: the dual benefit</strong>
        <p>A 2013 JISSN study found tongkat ali reduced cortisol by 16% in stressed adults. Since cortisol directly suppresses testosterone synthesis, this cortisol reduction amplifies the testosterone-boosting effect.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Clinically validated dosing</strong>
        <p>The most studied doses are 200 to 400mg of standardized extract daily. LJ100 (Physta) is the most-researched branded ingredient with over 14 human clinical trials published in peer-reviewed journals.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

