    <!-- SCIENCE SECTION -->
    <h2 id="science">The Science Behind Tongkat Ali: What Clinical Research Shows</h2>

    <p>Tongkat ali benefits from one of the strongest bodies of clinical evidence in the herbal testosterone support category. A 2022 meta-analysis in <em>Complementary Therapies in Medicine</em> analyzed nine randomized controlled trials and concluded that tongkat ali supplementation produces statistically significant increases in total testosterone compared to placebo. The evidence spans testosterone, cortisol, body composition, and sexual health.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Testosterone: strong evidence</strong>
        <p>A 2022 meta-analysis of 9 RCTs confirmed significant testosterone increases. The 2012 JISSN study showed a 37% increase in total testosterone with 200mg LJ100 daily for 4 weeks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Cortisol reduction: strong evidence</strong>
        <p>The same 2012 JISSN study demonstrated a 16% reduction in cortisol, improving the testosterone-to-cortisol ratio by 36% — a key marker of anabolic hormonal status.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Body composition: moderate evidence</strong>
        <p>A 2013 JISSN study found significant increases in lean body mass and strength in combination with resistance training at 400mg daily over 5 weeks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Sexual health: moderate evidence</strong>
        <p>Multiple studies report improved erectile function, sexual desire, and semen parameters at doses of 200 to 400mg daily over 4 to 12 weeks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Important context:</strong> Tongkat ali's testosterone effects are most pronounced in men with suboptimal testosterone levels due to stress, aging, or lifestyle factors. Young men with already-optimal testosterone levels may see less dramatic results. The cortisol reduction mechanism means that individuals under chronic stress may experience the greatest benefit, as cortisol suppression is a primary driver of age-related testosterone decline.</p>
    </div>

