    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Tongkat Ali Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is tongkat ali and what does it do?</summary>
      <p>Tongkat ali (<em>Eurycoma longifolia</em>) is a flowering plant native to Southeast Asian rainforests. Its root bark has been used for centuries as a tonic for energy and virility. Modern research identifies eurycomanone as the primary bioactive compound, supporting testosterone production by reducing SHBG, lowering cortisol, and supporting Leydig cell function. Clinical trials demonstrate improvements in testosterone, body composition, and stress markers.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Does tongkat ali really increase testosterone?</summary>
      <p>Yes. A 2022 meta-analysis of 9 RCTs in <em>Complementary Therapies in Medicine</em> confirmed significant testosterone increases. A 2012 JISSN study found 200mg LJ100 daily increased testosterone by 37% and reduced cortisol by 16% in moderately stressed adults over 4 weeks. The mechanism involves SHBG reduction, cortisol lowering, and Leydig cell support.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long does it take for tongkat ali to work?</summary>
      <p>Cortisol reduction and stress management effects typically appear within one to two weeks. Testosterone optimization and associated benefits become measurable at four to six weeks, with continued improvements through 12 weeks. A 2013 JISSN study showed significant strength and lean mass improvements after 5 weeks at 400mg daily combined with resistance training.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the recommended dosage for tongkat ali?</summary>
      <p>Clinical studies used 200 to 600mg of standardized extract daily. The most effective dose appears to be 400mg daily of a 100:1 or 200:1 extract standardized to minimum 2% eurycomanone. LJ100 (Physta) is the most-studied branded extract with over 14 human clinical trials.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is tongkat ali safe for long-term use?</summary>
      <p>Clinical trials lasting up to 12 weeks at 200 to 600mg daily show no adverse effects on liver function, kidney function, or blood chemistry. Cycling protocols (5 days on/2 days off or 8 weeks on/2 weeks off) are commonly recommended. Avoid if you have hormone-sensitive conditions, are pregnant, breastfeeding, or under 18.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What should I look for in a tongkat ali gummy?</summary>
      <p>Prioritize eurycomanone standardization (minimum 2%), verified extract concentration (100:1 or 200:1), Malaysian origin, and third-party testing. Patented ingredients like LJ100 (Physta) have the most clinical research backing. Clinically relevant dosing is 200 to 400mg of concentrated extract per serving.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can women take tongkat ali gummies?</summary>
      <p>Research suggests benefits for women including cortisol reduction, improved energy, and enhanced athletic performance at 200mg daily. Women with hormone-sensitive conditions (PCOS, hormone-receptor-positive cancers) should avoid tongkat ali. The standard dose for women is typically 100 to 200mg daily — lower than for men.</p>
    </details>

